'''Payovrata''' is the [[vrata]] or penance observed by [[Goddess]] [[Aditi]] to propitiate Lord [[Vishnu]]. 

==Ritual Activity==
It is usually observed for 12 days, and during that time the devotee subsists on a diet of milk alone. [http://vedabase.net/sb/8/16/en1]

==In Hindu Mythology==
A notable event is that of [[Wise old man|Sage]] [[Kashyap]] who asked his wife, [[Aditi]], to use this method to please [[Lord Narayana]] so that a solution could be found for her son who was defeated by the [[Asura]]s. This [[penance]] finally resulted in the [[Vamana]] [[Avatar]] sending [[Mahabali]] to the netherworld. [http://vedabase.net/sb/8/16/en1]

