'''Pindi''' are decked stones or tree stumps viewed in [[Hinduism]] as abstract manifestations of the mother goddess [[Shakti]]. Most of the 20th century goddess temples in [[Himachal Pradesh]], [[India]], enshrine a pindi.<ref>{{Citation
|publisher = Abhinav Publications |isbn = 8170174163 |publication-place = New Delhi, India |title = Images of Indian Goddesses |url = https://books.google.com/books?id=3SScwifhldQC |author = Madhu Bazaz Wangu |publication-date = 2003 |id = 8170174163 |pages = 158 }}</ref>

